ParoQuant is the state-of-the-art INT4 quantization for LLMs. It closes the accuracy gap with FP16 while running at near-AWQ speed. Supports NVIDIA GPUs (vLLM, Transformers) and Apple Silicon (MLX).

[`{{ paro_model_path }}`](https://huggingface.co/{{ paro_model_path }}) is a 4-bit [`{{ base_model }}`](https://huggingface.co/{{ base_model }}) quantized with [ParoQuant](https://github.com/z-lab/paroquant). Check out other ParoQuant models from the Hugging Face [collection](https://huggingface.co/collections/z-lab/paroquant). Swap the model name in the commands below to try any of them.


## Quick Start

### Installation

```bash
# NVIDIA GPU
pip install "paroquant[vllm]"

# Apple Silicon
pip install "paroquant[mlx]"
```

### Interactive Chat

```bash
python -m paroquant.cli.chat --model {{ paro_model_path }}
```

### OpenAI-Compatible API Server

```bash
python -m paroquant.cli.serve --model {{ paro_model_path }} --port 8000
```

{% if supports_tool_call -%}
### Agent with Tool Calling

Start the API server first, then install the agent dependencies and run:

```bash
pip install "paroquant[agent]"
python -m paroquant.cli.agent --model {{ paro_model_path }}
```

Tool use (web fetch, filesystem, time) requires [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en/download).
{%- endif %}

### Docker (NVIDIA GPU)

```bash
# Interactive chat
docker run --pull=always --rm -it --gpus all --ipc=host \
  ghcr.io/z-lab/paroquant:chat --model {{ paro_model_path }}

# API server (port 8000)
docker run --pull=always --rm -it --gpus all --ipc=host -p 8000:8000 \
  ghcr.io/z-lab/paroquant:serve --model {{ paro_model_path }}
```

